</div>
</p>
<p>Start like we always do, with lame, worn-out <code>$output-&gt;writeln('boring')</code>. Zip over
to the terminal and try that out:</p>
<pre><code class="language-bash"><div class="line">./bin/console styles:play</div></code></pre>
<p>And there it is! In all its white text on a black background glory.</p>
<h2 id="introducing-symfonystyle">Introducing SymfonyStyle <a class="headerlink" href="console-styling#introducing-symfonystyle" title="Permalink to this headline"><i class="fa fa-link" aria-hidden="true"></i></a></h2>
<p>Enough of that! That still works, it will always work. But now, create a new <code>$style</code>
variable set to <code>new SymfonyStyle()</code>. Pass it the <code>$input</code> and <code>$output</code>:</p>
<p><div class="code-block-wrapper" data-code-block-guid="cfdb0f47ab">
