<p>Let's try it! Run:</p>
<pre><code class="language-bash"><div class="line">./bin/console styles:play</div></code></pre>
<p>OooOOooooOOO. Without doing anything, Javier gives us the console equivalent of
<code>h1</code> and <code>h2</code> tags, with colors and separation. Below, it's subtle, but all the text
lines are indented with one space to make them stand out. The note starts with an
exclamation point and uses a hip color.</p>
<p>Get the idea?</p>
