<h2 id="success-and-error-messages">Success and Error Messages <a class="headerlink" href="console-styling#success-and-error-messages" title="Permalink to this headline"><i class="fa fa-link" aria-hidden="true"></i></a></h2>
<p>Time to take the fancy up a notch! Add another section for some BIG messages.
SymfonyStyle has built-in methods to emphasize that "things are great!", "things are terrible!
or "OMG things are <em>really</em> terrible". Start with <code>$style-&gt;success('I &lt;3 Lorem ipsum');</code>:</p>
