<p>Creating tables isn't new, but <code>$style</code> has a shortcut where Javier styles them for us.
Thanks Javier!</p>
<p>Use <code>$style-&gt;table()</code>. The first argument holds the headers: <code>['User', 'Birthday'],</code>
and the second argument holds the rows. Plug in an important birthday to remember:
<code>['weaverryan','June 5th']</code> and an even <em>more</em> important one to remember,
<code>['leannapelham','All of February']</code>. That's right, the celebration for Leanna never
ends:</p>
