<p>So let's see how this renders!</p>
<pre><code class="language-bash"><div class="line">./bin/console styles:play</div></code></pre>
<p>Wow, look at that table: nice spacing, nice styled headers. Of course you could do
this all yourself, but why?</p>
<p>Ok, time for just <em>one</em> more: a list of my favorite things:
<code>$style-&gt;text('Ryan\'s my favorite things')</code> with a nicely-styled list. Use
<code>$style-&gt;listing([])</code>. Pass this an array, which you can think of as an unordered
list. Let's see, I like <code>['Running', 'Pizza', 'Watching Leanna tease Jordi Boggiano',]</code>:</p>
<p><div class="code-block-wrapper" data-code-block-guid="fc9ed57c08">
    <div class="meta">
        <div class="actions">
